  "text": "The monoclonal antibody to GPTG, CUB 7402, was a gift from Dr. Paul J. Birckbichler [CITATION_1] , Oklahoma Medical Research Foundation, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, and was also purchased (NeoMarkers, Lab Vision Corporation, Fremont, California). CUB 7402 cross-reacts with TG from a variety of species, including human [CITATION_2] . Another antibody to TG, TG100, was also obtained from this source. Combinations of TG100 and CUB 7402 (MS-300; NeoMarkers, Lab Vision Corporation) were also used for immunoblotting. The previously characterized IgM murine monoclonal antibody to the N⑀(␥-glutamyl)lysine isopeptide, TG activity standard curve. A colorimetric assay for transglutaminase was established, using guinea pig liver transglutaminase (GPTG) as the standard enzyme. The assay is based on the incorporation of 5-biotinamindopentylamine into immobilized N, NЈ-dimethylcasein, as described in \"Materials and Methods.\" The assay was linear between 0 and 1 g/ml of GPTG. This assay was used to determine the activity of transglutaminase in coronary artery atherectomy tissue (Table 2) .",
